Global requirements:
- Keep the app usable when backend is offline through mock fallback.
- Show mock fallback banner when mock data is used.
- Show dry-run/read-only/approval-required states clearly.
- Make kill switch/halt state visually prominent.
- Make social approval and dry-run state visually prominent.
- Make IoT dry-run and confirmation state visually prominent.
- Show backtest disclaimer: “Backtest results are not guaranteed future performance.”
- Keep tests deterministic and offline.
- Keep frontend production build excluding test files via tsconfig.build.json.
- Use npm test only; do not run npm test -- --run.

Validation for every sub-phase:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

cd ../frontend
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm use 20
npm test
npm run build

